'''安然丑闻案'''曝光于2001年10月，最终导致总部位于[[德克萨斯州|德克萨斯州]][[休斯顿|休斯顿]]的美国能源公司[[安然公司|安然公司]][[破产|破产]]，并连锁导致一度贵为[[四大_(會計師行)|全球五大]][[审计|审计]][[会计|会计]]事务所之一的[[安达信会计师事务所|安达信会计师事务所]]解体。这个丑闻既是美国历史上最大破产案，也是最大的审计失败事件。<ref name="DarkSide61">{{Cite journal|last = Bratton|first = William W.|title = Does Corporate Law Protect the Interests of Shareholders and Other Stakeholders?: Enron and the Dark Side of Shareholder Value|journal = [[Tulane_Law_Review|Tulane Law Review]]|volume = |issue = 1275|page = 61|publisher = [[Tulane_University_Law_School|Tulane University Law School]]|location = New Orleans|date = May 2002|url = http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=301475|format = PDF|doi = |accessdate = 2010-10-12|archive-date = 2010-12-12|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101212002017/http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=301475|dead-url = no}}</ref>

安然于1985年由[[肯尼思·萊|肯尼思·萊]]（Kenneth Lay）在合并休斯顿能源公司和 InterNorth 能源公司的基础上成立。几年后[[杰弗里·斯基林|杰弗里·斯基林]]（Jeffrey Skilling）加入公司。他组织了一个高管团队，通过利用会计规范上的漏洞、特别目的事业体、和低劣的会计报告来掩盖公司合同与项目失败带来的数十亿美元债务。[[首席财务官|首席财务官]]安德鲁·法斯托（Andrew Fastow）和其他高级职员不仅在高风险会计行为上误导了安然的董事会和审计委员会，还向安达信施压使其忽视这些问题。

安然的投资者在公司破产之后向法院提出了400亿美元的诉讼，而安然的股价也从2000年中的每股90.75美元暴跌到2001年11月底的不到1美元。<ref name="Enron">{{Cite journal|last = |first = |title = Enron shareholders look to SEC for support in court|journal = [[New_York_Times|New York Times]]|volume = |issue = |page = |publisher = [[New_York_Times|New York Times]]|location = |date = May 2007|url = http://www.nytimes.com/2007/05/10/business/worldbusiness/10iht-enron.1.5648578.html?_r=0|format = WEB|doi = |accessdate = 7 May 2013|archive-date = 2020-11-24|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201124021137/https://www.nytimes.com/2007/05/10/business/worldbusiness/10iht-enron.1.5648578.html?_r=0|dead-url = no}}</ref>[[美国证券交易委员会|美国证券交易委员会]]（SEC）对安然启动调查同时，其同城的竞争对手Dynegy也发起了价格极低的收购。在收购失败后，安然于2001年12月2日根据美国破产法第11章宣布破产。拥有634亿美元资产的安然也一度成为美国最大的破产案，直到翌年的世通公司破产案发生为止。<ref name="Quality12">{{Cite journal|last = Benston|first = George J.|title = The Quality of Corporate Financial Statements and Their Auditors Before and After Enron|journal = Policy Analysis|volume = |issue = 497|page = 12|publisher = [[Cato_Institute|Cato Institute]]|location = Washington D.C.|date = November 6, 2003|url = http://www.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa497.pdf|format = PDF|doi = |accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ00qIbE?url=http://www.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa497.pdf|archivedate = 2010-10-18|dead-url = no}}</ref>

许多安然的高级职员都面临多项欺詐指控，其中一些人也被判有罪入狱。安然的审计公司安达信会计师事务所，也被美国地方法院以非法销毁文件妨碍美国证券交易委员会调查而被判吊销执照。虽然[[美国最高法院|美国最高法院]]随后推翻了安达信部分的有罪判决，但是安达信已经失去了大多数客户的信任而宣布停业。安然的职工和持股者损失了数以亿计美金的养老金和股票，诉讼只帮助他们挽回了很小一部分损失。

这场丑闻之后，美国对上市公司的财会报告的准确度发布了众多新法规。<ref name="Ayala1">{{cite journal|last=Ayala |first=Astrid |author2=Giancarlo Ibárgüen, Snr |title=A Market Proposal for Auditing the Financial Statements of Public Companies |journal=Journal of Management of Value |page=1 |publisher=[[Universidad_Francisco_Marroquín|Universidad Francisco Marroquín]] |date=March 2006 |url=http://www.mba.ufm.edu.gt/journalofmanagement/content/ENG_MarketProposal.pdf |access-date=October 17, 2010 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0THjI8?url=http://www.mba.ufm.edu.gt/journalofmanagement/content/ENG_MarketProposal.pdf |archive-date=October 18, 2010 |url-status=dead}}</ref> 其中一份重要的法案，[[萨班斯-奥克斯利法案|萨班斯-奥克斯利法案]]，提高了对销毁、篡改、编造财会记录以试图妨碍联邦调查和欺骗股东的惩罚力度。<ref name="Trends5">{{Cite journal|last = Cohen|first = Daniel A.|author2 = Dey Aiyesha|author3 = Thomas Z. Lys|title = Trends in Earnings Management and Informativeness of Earnings Announcements in the Pre- and Post-Sarbanes Oxley Periods|journal = |volume = |issue = |page = 5|publisher = [[Kellogg_School_of_Management|Kellogg School of Management]]|location = Evanston, Illinois|date = February 2005|url = http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=658782|doi = |accessdate = 2010-10-13|archive-date = 2010-10-05|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101005044050/http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=658782|dead-url = no}}</ref>这项法案也对审计公司的公正独立性提出了更高的要求。<ref name="Ayala1"/> 以求杜絕此類詐欺事件的發生。

== 安然的崛起 ==
[[File:Ken_Lay.jpg|right]]
1985年, [[肯尼思·萊|肯尼思·萊]]在合并休斯顿天然气公司的[[管输工艺|天然气管线]]和InterNorth的基础上创建了安然。<ref name="Healy3">{{Cite journal|last = Healy|first = Paul M.|author2 = Krishna G. Palepu|title = The Fall of Enron|journal = [[Journal_of_Economic_Perspectives|Journal of Economic Perspectives]]|volume = 17|issue = 2|page = 3|date = Spring 2003|url = http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf|format = PDF|doi = 10.1257/089533003765888403|accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0YEF6T?url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf|archivedate = 2010-10-18|dead-url = no}}</ref> 1990年代初，他帮助建立了电力市场交易四通，之后美国国会立法规范了天然气的交易。这使得像安然这样的天然气公司可以以更高的价格销售天然气，因此大幅提高了公司的收入。<ref name="StruggleNYT">{{Cite news|last = Gerth|first = Jeff|author2 = Richard A. Oppel, Jr.|url = http://www.nytimes.com/2001/11/10/business/regulators-struggle-with-a-marketplace-created-by-enron.html|work = [[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|title = Regulators struggle with a marketplace created by Enron|date = 2001-11-10|accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0jjwFo?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2001/11/10/business/regulators-struggle-with-a-marketplace-created-by-enron.html|archivedate = 2010-10-18|dead-url = no}}</ref> 在其他天然气生产商和地方政府的呼吁对天然气价格波动提高监管的同时，安然等生产商极力阻挠这样的新规。<ref name="StruggleNYT">{{Cite news|last = Gerth|first = Jeff|author2 = Richard A. Oppel, Jr.|url = http://www.nytimes.com/2001/11/10/business/regulators-struggle-with-a-marketplace-created-by-enron.html|work = [[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|title = Regulators struggle with a marketplace created by Enron|date = 2001-11-10|accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = http://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0jjwFo|archivedate = 2010-10-17}}</ref><ref name="SurestStepsNYT">{{Cite news|last = Banerjee|first = Neela|url = http://www.nytimes.com/2001/11/09/business/surest-steps-not-the-swiftest-are-propelling-dynegy-past-enron.html|title = Surest steps, not the swiftest, are propelling Dynegy past Enron|work = The New York Times|date = 2001-11-09|accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0nANUu?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2001/11/09/business/surest-steps-not-the-swiftest-are-propelling-dynegy-past-enron.html|archivedate = 2010-10-18|dead-url = no}}</ref>

安然于1992年的天然气合同税前收入高达1亿2200万美金，使其成为北美最大的天然气销售商，天然气销售收入也成为公司第二大收入来源。而1999年11月开通的安然在线交易网站使公司能够更好地管理交易合同。<ref name="Healy7">{{Cite journal|last = Healy|first = Paul M.|author2 = Krishna G. Palepu|title = The Fall of Enron|journal = [[Journal_of_Economic_Perspectives|Journal of Economic Perspectives]]|volume = 17|issue = 2|page = 7|date = Spring 2003|url = http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf|format = PDF|accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0YEF6T?url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf|archivedate = 2010-10-18|doi = 10.1257/089533003765888403|dead-url = no}}</ref>

在试图追求进一步发展的过程中，安然选择了分散投资的策略。公司在全球拥有并运营了各种业务，包括天然气管线，电厂，木浆与纸张生产，水厂和网路服务等等。公司也通过销售相关合同获得更大的利益。<ref name="Healy5">{{Cite journal|last = Healy|first = Paul M.|author2 = Krishna G. Palepu|title = The Fall of Enron|journal = [[Journal_of_Economic_Perspectives|Journal of Economic Perspectives]]|volume = 17|issue = 2|page = 5|date = Spring 2003|url = http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf|format = PDF|accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0YEF6T?url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf|archivedate = 2010-10-18|doi = 10.1257/089533003765888403|dead-url = no}}</ref>

安然的股票从1990年代到1998年年底仅仅上涨了311%，只比[[标准普尔500指数|标准普尔500指数]]的平均值高一些。<ref name="Healy1">{{Cite journal|last = Healy|first = Paul M.|author2 = Krishna G. Palepu|title = The Fall of Enron|journal = [[Journal_of_Economic_Perspectives|Journal of Economic Perspectives]]|volume = 17|issue = 2|page = 1|date = Spring 2003|url = http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf|format = PDF|accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0YEF6T?url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf|archivedate = 2010-10-18|doi = 10.1257/089533003765888403|dead-url = no}}</ref> 但是，安然的股票在1999年增长了56%，并在2000年进一步达到了87%的增长，相比于标准普尔指数在1999年的20%的增长和2000年的10%下跌显得极为成功。2000年12月31日为止，安然的股票已经价值每股83.13美元，其市场价值也高达600亿美金，这达到了安然收入的70倍，账面价值的6倍。不仅如此，安然在[[财富杂志|财富杂志]]的调查中被评为全美最具创新精神的公司。<ref name="Healy1">{{Cite journal|last = Healy|first = Paul M.|author2 = Krishna G. Palepu|title = The Fall of Enron|journal = [[Journal_of_Economic_Perspectives|Journal of Economic Perspectives]]|volume = 17|issue = 2|page = 1|date = Spring 2003|url = http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf|format = PDF|accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = http://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0YEF6T|archivedate = 2010-10-17|doi = 10.1257/089533003765888403}}</ref>

== 失败的原因 ==
安然复杂的金融报告系统严重迷惑了持股者和分析师。<ref name="DarkSide6">{{Cite journal|last = Bratton|first = William W.|title = Does Corporate Law Protect the Interests of Shareholders and Other Stakeholders?: Enron and the Dark Side of Shareholder Value|journal = [[Tulane_Law_Review|Tulane Law Review]]|volume = |issue = 1275|page = 6|publisher = [[Tulane_University_Law_School|Tulane University Law School]]|location = New Orleans|date = May 2002|url = http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=301475|format = PDF|doi = |accessdate = 2010-10-12|archive-date = 2010-12-12|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101212002017/http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=301475|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="MackOther">{{Cite news|last = Mack|first = Toni|url = http://www.forbes.com/forbes/2002/1014/062_print.html|work = [[Forbes_(magazine)|Forbes]]|title = The Other Enron Story|date = 2002-10-14|accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0qQyoO?url=http://www.forbes.com/forbes/2002/1014/062_print.html|archivedate = 2010-10-18|dead-url = no}}</ref> 此外，其複雜的業務模式和不道德的行為使之利用會計限制來歪曲收益和修改資產負債表，借此顯示出良好的業績。<ref name="Healy9">{{Cite journal|last = Healy|first = Paul M.|author2 = Krishna G. Palepu|title = The Fall of Enron|journal = [[Journal_of_Economic_Perspectives|Journal of Economic Perspectives]]|volume = 17|issue = 2|page = 9|date = Spring 2003|url = http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf|format = PDF|accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0YEF6T?url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf|archivedate = 2010-10-18|doi = 10.1257/089533003765888403|dead-url = no}}</ref>

许多问题一起导致了公司的破产，而这些问题都在肯尼思·萊、杰弗里·斯基林、安德鲁·法斯托及其他高层直接或间接知情的情况下发生。肯尼思·萊在公司倒闭前的几年中担任董事长，是他批准了杰弗里·斯基林和安德鲁·法斯托的违法行为，即使他并不过问每个细节。杰弗里·斯基林只顾满足华尔街的预期，支持使用[[调至市价|调至市价]]的会计方法（该方法基于后来膨胀了的市场价值），并且对高管施压要求他们寻找各种方法隐瞒债务。法斯托和其他高管“创造资产负债表外项目的媒介、复杂的融资结构与交易，这些东西令人困惑到没人能理解他们。”<ref name="McLean1323">{{Cite book|title = [[Enron:_The_Smartest_Guys_in_the_Room|Enron: The Smartest Guys in the Room]]|last = McLean|first = Bethany|author2 = Peter Elkind|pages = 132–133|isbn = 1-59184-008-2}}</ref>

=== 收入确认 ===
安然和其他能源提供商通过提供批发销售能源、[[风险管理|风险管理]]、建造和管理电厂、天然气管线、天然气贮藏和处理工厂等服务获得利润.<ref name="FossRevol">{{Cite journal|last = Foss|first = Michelle Michot|title = Enron and the Energy Market Revolution|journal = |volume = |issue = |page = 1|publisher = [[University_of_Houston_Law_Center|University of Houston Law Center]]|location = |date = September 2003|url = http://www.beg.utexas.edu/energyecon/energy-inc/members/Course_Modules/Class_Info/Foss_Enron%20Chapter_Final_9%205%2003.pdf|doi = |accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0uZXuG?url=http://www.beg.utexas.edu/energyecon/energy-inc/members/Course_Modules/Class_Info/Foss_Enron%20Chapter_Final_9%205%2003.pdf|archivedate = 2010-10-18|dead-url = yes}}</ref> 在接受买卖风险的同时，贸易商将销售价格记为收入，将成本计入销售成本中。与之相对的，一名“中介”在提供服务的同时并不承担这样的买卖风险。而这个“中介”，此时也就是服务提供商，可以将其代理收入计入自己的收入当中，而不能是整个交易的价值。<ref name="DharanRed102">{{Cite journal|last = Dharan|first = Bala G.|author2 = William R. Bufkins|title = Red Flags in Enron's Reporting of Revenues and Key Financial Measures|pages = 101–103|publisher = [[Social_Science_Research_Network|Social Science Research Network]]|date = July 2008|url = http://www.ruf.rice.edu/~bala/files/dharan-bufkins_enron_red_flags.pdf|doi = |accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0yCA9i?url=http://www.ruf.rice.edu/~bala/files/dharan-bufkins_enron_red_flags.pdf|archivedate = 2010-10-18|journal = |dead-url = no}}</ref></div>

虽然如[[高盛|高盛]]和[[美林证券|美林证券]]等交易公司使用传统的“中介模型”（也就是在收入中只计入委托费用），安然却将整个交易的价值计入了自己的收入。而这个所谓的“贸易商模型”被认为更据侵略性。<ref name="autogenerated1">{{Cite journal|last = Dharan|first = Bala G.|author2 = William R. Bufkins|title = Red Flags in Enron's Reporting of Revenues and Key Financial Measures|page = 102|publisher = Social Science Research Network|date = July 2008|url = http://www.ruf.rice.edu/~bala/files/dharan-bufkins_enron_red_flags.pdf|doi = |accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0yCA9i?url=http://www.ruf.rice.edu/~bala/files/dharan-bufkins_enron_red_flags.pdf|archivedate = 2010-10-18|journal = |dead-url = no}}</ref> 安然的这种虚高收入的办法很快被能源交易产业的其他公司所采用，以保持和这家收入大幅提高的公司的竞争能力。其他能源公司，包括 Duke Energy、Reliant Energy、和Dynegy在改变记录方法以后都和安然一起在[[财富美国500强|财富美国500强]]排名中稳坐最富有公司前50的位置。<ref name="DharanRed105">{{Cite journal|last = Dharan|first = Bala G.|author2 = William R. Bufkins|title = Red Flags in Enron's Reporting of Revenues and Key Financial Measures|page = 105|publisher = Social Science Research Network|date = July 2008|url = http://www.ruf.rice.edu/~bala/files/dharan-bufkins_enron_red_flags.pdf|doi = |accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0yCA9i?url=http://www.ruf.rice.edu/~bala/files/dharan-bufkins_enron_red_flags.pdf|archivedate = 2010-10-18|journal = |dead-url = no}}</ref>

1996至2000年间，安然的收入增加了超过7.5倍，从1996年的133亿美元直达2000年的1008亿美元。这种年增长65%的发展速度在行业内是前所未见的，在能源行业年增长在2%到3%的公司都不常见。仅2001年前九个月，安然就报告了1387亿美元的收入，在[[财富世界500强|财富世界500强]]中达到第六位。<ref name="DharanRed97100">{{Cite journal|last = Dharan|first = Bala G.|author2 = William R. Bufkins|title = Red Flags in Enron's Reporting of Revenues and Key Financial Measures|pages = 97–100|publisher = Social Science Research Network|date = July 2008|url = http://www.ruf.rice.edu/~bala/files/dharan-bufkins_enron_red_flags.pdf|doi = |accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0yCA9i?url=http://www.ruf.rice.edu/~bala/files/dharan-bufkins_enron_red_flags.pdf|archivedate = 2010-10-18|journal = |dead-url = no}}</ref>

=== 调至市价的会计方法 ===
本来在安然的天然气业务中，会计计算十分简单，只需记录每一会计期间公司的实际销售成本和收入。然而，当斯基林加入公司之后，他要求公司使用调至市价的会计方法来体现他口中的所谓“真实的经济价值”。<ref name="McLean3942">{{Cite book|title = [[Enron:_The_Smartest_Guys_in_the_Room|Enron: The Smartest Guys in the Room]]|last = McLean|first = Bethany|author2 = Peter Elkind|pages = 39–42|isbn = 1-59184-008-2}}</ref> 安然则成为了第一家使用此种方法记录其复杂长期合同的非金融机构。<ref name="MackRisk">{{Cite news|last = Mack|first = Toni|url = http://proquest.umi.com.libproxy.sdsu.edu/pqdweb?did=421703&sid=3&Fmt=3&clientId=17862&RQT=309&VName=PQD|registration = yes|work = [[Forbes_(magazine)|Forbes]]|title = Hidden Risks|date = 1993-05-24|accessdate = 2010-10-16}}</ref> 调至市价的会计方法要求，当一份长期合同签订时，其估计收入使用未来现金流的净现值衡量。通常这些合同的可行性和相关成本是难以衡量的。<ref name="Healy10">{{Cite journal|last = Healy|first = Paul M.|author2 = Krishna G. Palepu|title = The Fall of Enron|journal = [[Journal_of_Economic_Perspectives|Journal of Economic Perspectives]]|volume = 17|issue = 2|page = 10|date = Spring 2003|url = http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf|format = PDF|accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0YEF6T?url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf|archivedate = 2010-10-18|doi = 10.1257/089533003765888403|dead-url = no}}</ref> 为了使利润和现金流间的巨大差异相匹配，投资者往往获得错误的或具有误导性的报告。在使用此种方法时，项目的收入会被记录，虽然公司并没有收到现金，并且会增加账面上的财务收益。但是在之后几年，利润却不能被计入，所以就需要其他的新项目来继续提高账面收入以满足投资者的期望。<ref name="McLean3942">{{Cite book|title = [[Enron:_The_Smartest_Guys_in_the_Room|Enron: The Smartest Guys in the Room]]|last = McLean|first = Bethany|author2 = Peter Elkind|pages = 39–42|isbn = 1-59184-008-2}}</ref> 正如安然的一个竞争对手所提到的，“如果你想加速你的收入，你就必须在未来做越来越多的交易来展示相同或更多的收入。”<ref name="MackRisk">{{Cite news|last = Mack|first = Toni|url = http://proquest.umi.com.libproxy.sdsu.edu/pqdweb?did=421703&sid=3&Fmt=3&clientId=17862&RQT=309&VName=PQD|registration = yes|work = [[Forbes_(magazine)|Forbes]]|title = Hidden Risks|date = 1993-05-24|accessdate = 2010-10-16}}</ref> 虽然有潜在隐患，[[美国证券交易委员会|美国证券交易委员会]]还是于1992年1月30日批准安然在天然气期货交易合同中使用这一会计方法。<ref name="McLean3942">{{Cite book|title = [[Enron:_The_Smartest_Guys_in_the_Room|Enron: The Smartest Guys in the Room]]|last = McLean|first = Bethany|author2 = Peter Elkind|pages = 39–42|isbn = 1-59184-008-2}}</ref> 但是，之后安然却将这种方法推广到公司其他业务领域以满足华尔街投资者的预期。<ref name="McLean127">{{Cite book|title = [[Enron:_The_Smartest_Guys_in_the_Room|Enron: The Smartest Guys in the Room]]|last = McLean|first = Bethany|author2 = Peter Elkind|page = 127|isbn = 1-59184-008-2}}</ref>

以一份2000年七月的合同为例，安然和[[百視達|百視達]]签订了一份20年的合同，内容是年终时在美国各城市推广按需娱乐节目的服务。在几个试探性的项目之后，安然确认了该交易超过1亿1千万美元预计利润，虽然分析师质疑该项目技术上的可行性和市场对这种服务的需求。<ref name="Healy10">{{Cite journal|last = Healy|first = Paul M.|author2 = Krishna G. Palepu|title = The Fall of Enron|journal = [[Journal_of_Economic_Perspectives|Journal of Economic Perspectives]]|volume = 17|issue = 2|page = 10|date = Spring 2003|url = http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf|format = PDF|accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = http://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0YEF6T|archivedate = 2010-10-17|doi = 10.1257/089533003765888403}}</ref> 当该网络无法运作时，百视通终止了合同，而安然却在继续记录未来利润，即使实际上这份合同已经带来了巨大损失。<ref name="BlockbusterUSA">{{Cite news|last = Hays|first = Kristen|url = http://www.usatoday.com/tech/techinvestor/corporatenews/2005-04-17-new-enron-trial_x.htm|work = [[USA_Today|USA Today]]|title = Next Enron trial focuses on broadband unit|date = 2005-04-17|accessdate = 2010-10-17|archiveurl = https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ1Btmp1?url=http://www.usatoday.com/tech/techinvestor/corporatenews/2005-04-17-new-enron-trial_x.htm|archivedate = 2010-10-18|dead-url = no}}</ref>

=== 特殊目的实体 ===
安然使用特殊目的实体——有限合伙企业或公司，来满足为特定[[资产|资产]]融资或管理风险的临时或特定目的。该公司选择披露其使用的“特殊目的实体”的极少信息。<ref name="Healy11">{{cite journal |last=Healy |first=Paul M. |author2=Krishna G. Palepu |title=The Fall of Enron |journal=[[Journal_of_Economic_Perspectives|Journal of Economic Perspectives]] |volume=17 |issue=2 |page=11 |date=Spring 2003 |url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf |format=PDF |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0YEF6T?url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf |archivedate=2010-10-18 |doi=10.1257/089533003765888403 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 这些空壳公司由赞助商创立，借助独立的[[私人股权投资|股权投资者]]和债务融资为其提供资金。对于财务报告目的，有一系列规则指示特殊目的实体是否需与赞助商独立。总体而言，到2001年安然公司已使用过数百家特殊目的实体来隐藏债务。<ref name="Healy10"/> 安然采用过许多特殊目的实体，如 Thomas 和 Condor 避税地的合伙企业，基于Apache协议的金融资产证券化投资信托基金（financial asset securitization investment trusts，FASITs），斯蒂尔交易中的房地产抵押贷款投资渠道（real estate mortgage investment conduits，REMICs），科奇斯交易中的REMICs和房地产投资信托基金（real estate investment trusts，REITs）。<ref>{{cite book | title= After Enron: Lessons for Public Policy | first= William A. | last= Niskanen | year= 2007 | pages= 306–307 | publisher= Rowman & Littlefield | isbn= 978-0-7425-4434-5 | url= http://books.google.com/books?id=9rBTY25Q5ncC&pg=PA306 | access-date= 2016-02-19 | archive-date= 2020-12-04 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201204104723/https://books.google.com/books?id=9rBTY25Q5ncC&pg=PA306 | dead-url= no }}</ref>

特殊目的实体不仅仅被用于规避会计惯例。违反会计惯例的结果之一是，安然公司的资产负债表低估了其[[负债|负债]]，高估了其[[权益|权益]]及收益。<ref name="Healy11"/> 安然向股东披露，其已使用特殊目的主体[[对冲|对冲]]掉了非流动性投资的下行风险。然而，投资者忽视了这样一个事实，特殊目的主体实际上是采用安然公司自己的股票和资金担保来为这些对冲交易融资。这不会使安然免受下行风险的影响。<ref name="Healy11"/> 安然使用的特殊目的实体中比较有名的包括JEDI、Chewco、Whitewing 和 [[LJM|LJM]] 。

==== JEDI 和 Chewco ====
1993年，安然公司与加利福尼亚州养老基金（California state pension fund，[[CalPERS|CalPERS]]）建立了能源投资领域的合资企业，联合能源发展投资（ Joint Energy Development Investments，JEDI）。<ref name="McLean67">{{cite book|title=[[Enron:_The_Smartest_Guys_in_the_Room|Enron: The Smartest Guys in the Room]]|last=McLean|first=Bethany|author2=Peter Elkind|page=[https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle/page/67 67]|isbn=1-59184-008-2}}</ref> 1997年，担任首席运营官（COO）的斯基林要求CalPERS将安然加入一项单独投资。CalPERS对这个想法很有兴趣，但此事只有当它终止与安然在JEDI的合作关系时才能实现。<ref name="DarkSide30">{{cite journal|last=Bratton|first=William W.|title=Does Corporate Law Protect the Interests of Shareholders and Other Stakeholders?: Enron and the Dark Side of Shareholder Value|journal=[[Tulane_Law_Review|Tulane Law Review]]|volume=|issue=1275|page=30|publisher=[[Tulane_University_Law_School|Tulane University Law School]]|location=New Orleans|date=May 2002|url=http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=301475|format=PDF|doi=|accessdate=2010-10-12|archive-date=2010-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101212002017/http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=301475|dead-url=no}}</ref> 然而安然并不想让CalPERS的股份承担JEDI资产负债表中的任何债务。于是首席财务官（CFO）法斯托开设了一家特殊目的主体，Chewco投资有限合伙企业（Chewco Investments limited partnership，L.P.），由安然担保进行债务融资并以3.83亿美元获得CalPERS在合资企业的股权。<ref name="Healy11"/> 由于法斯托创建的Chewco，JEDI的亏损不会体现在安然的资产负债表上。

2001年秋天，CalPERS和安然公司的协议被揭露，协议要求对Chewco和JEDI废止安然的之前会计方法。这次取消资格揭示出，安然报告的1997至2001年中期的盈利将需要下调4.05亿美元，债务需增加6.28亿美元。<ref name="DarkSide31">{{cite journal|last=Bratton|first=William W.|title=Does Corporate Law Protect the Interests of Shareholders and Other Stakeholders?: Enron and the Dark Side of Shareholder Value|journal=[[Tulane_Law_Review|Tulane Law Review]]|volume=|issue=1275|page=31|publisher=[[Tulane_University_Law_School|Tulane University Law School]]|location=New Orleans|date=May 2002|url=http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=301475|format=PDF|doi=|accessdate=2010-10-12|archive-date=2010-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101212002017/http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=301475|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==== Whitewing ====
Whitewing是安然用作融资手段的一家特殊目的实体。<ref name="WhiteWing">{{cite journal |last=McCullough |first=Robert |title=Understanding Whitewing |page=1 |publisher=McCullough Research |location=Portland, Oregon |date=January 2002 |url=http://www.mresearch.com/pdfs/13.pdf |format=PDF |doi= |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ1HEEuA?url=http://www.mresearch.com/pdfs/13.pdf |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes |journal= }}</ref> 1997年12月，安然公司出资5.79亿美元和外部投资者出资5亿美元创立了Whitewing Associates L.P.。两年后，该实体的协议被更改以使之不再与安然公司有联系，也不会计入安然的资产负债表。Whitewing被用于购买安然公司的资产，包括在电厂的股份、管道、股票和其他投资。<ref name="Cornford18">{{cite journal |last=Cornford |first=Andrew |title=Internationally Agreed Principles For Corporate Governance And The Enron Case |journal=G-24 Discussion Paper Series No. 30 |page=18 |publisher=[[United_Nations_Conference_on_Trade_and_Development|United Nations Conference on Trade and Development]] |location=New York |date=June 2004 |url=http://www.unctad.org/en/docs/gdsmdpbg2420046_en.pdf |format=PDF |doi= |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ1KQjhV?url=http://www.unctad.org/en/docs/gdsmdpbg2420046_en.pdf |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 1999和2001年间，Whitewing购买了安然价值20亿美元的资产，使用安然股票作为[[抵押|抵押]]。虽然这次交易经由安然公司董事会批准，但该资产转让并非真实销售，本应作为贷款处理。<ref name="Lambert35">{{cite book|last=Lambert|first=Jeremiah D.|title=Energy Companies and Market Reform|publisher=[[PennWell_Corporation|PennWell Corporation]]|location=[[Tulsa|Tulsa]]|date=September 2006|page=35|isbn=1-59370-060-1}}</ref>

==== LJM 和 Raptors ====
1999年，法斯托策划了两家[[有限合伙企业|有限合伙企业]]：LJM Cayman. L.P.（LJM1）和LJM2 Co-Investment L.P.（LJM2）。这是为了买入安然业绩不佳的股票和股份以改善其财务报表。创建LJM 1 和LJM 2 只是将他们作为安然使用的特殊目的主体所需的外部投资者。<ref name="DarkSide31"/> 法斯托不得不从董事会取得对《[http://mishkenot.org.il/Hebrew/docs/ethics/%D7%A7%D7%95%D7%93%D7%99%D7%9D%20%D7%90%D7%AA%D7%99%D7%99%D7%9D%20%D7%A9%D7%9C%20%D7%90%D7%A8%D7%92%D7%95%D7%A0%D7%99%D7%9D%20%D7%A2%D7%A1%D7%A7%D7%99%D7%99%D7%9D/Enron%20Code%20Of%20Ethics.pdf 安然伦理准则] {{Wayback|url=http://mishkenot.org.il/Hebrew/docs/ethics/%D7%A7%D7%95%D7%93%D7%99%D7%9D%20%D7%90%D7%AA%D7%99%D7%99%D7%9D%20%D7%A9%D7%9C%20%D7%90%D7%A8%D7%92%D7%95%D7%A0%D7%99%D7%9D%20%D7%A2%D7%A1%D7%A7%D7%99%D7%99%D7%9D/Enron%20Code%20Of%20Ethics.pdf |date=20201204113856 }}》的豁免（因为他拥有CFO的头衔）以管理这些公司。<ref name="McLean1937">{{cite book|title=[[Enron:_The_Smartest_Guys_in_the_Room|Enron: The Smartest Guys in the Room]]|last=McLean|first=Bethany|author2=Peter Elkind|page=[https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle/page/193 193] and 197|isbn=1-59184-008-2}}</ref> [[美联银行|美联银行]]、[[摩根大通|摩根大通]]、[[瑞士信贷第一波士顿|瑞士信贷第一波士顿]]、[[花旗集团|花旗集团]]和其他投资者为这两家合伙企业提供了约3.9亿美元的融资。证券销售商[[美林证券|美林证券]]出资2200万美元。<ref name="DarkSide31"/>

“Raptor I-IV”是四家LJM相关的特殊目的实体，以[[侏罗纪公园|侏罗纪公园]]中的[[迅猛龙|迅猛龙]]命名。安然向“Raptor I-IV”转移了超过“12亿美元的资产，包括数百万股安然的[[普通股|普通股]]和购买数百万股这些股票的长期权利，加上安然150亿的[[应付票据|应付票据]]”。这些披露在公司的财务报表附注中。<ref name="Velociraptors">{{cite news |last=Levine |first=Greg |url=http://www.forbes.com/2006/03/07/enron-fastow-two-cx_gl_0307autofacescan16.html |work=[[Forbes|Forbes]] |title=Fastow Tells Of Loss-Hiding Enron 'Raptors' |date=2006-03-07 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ1O8XIc?url=http://www.forbes.com/2006/03/07/enron-fastow-two-cx_gl_0307autofacescan16.html |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref name="DarkSide33">{{cite journal|last=Bratton|first=William W.|title=Does Corporate Law Protect the Interests of Shareholders and Other Stakeholders?: Enron and the Dark Side of Shareholder Value|journal=[[Tulane_Law_Review|Tulane Law Review]]|volume=|issue=1275|page=33|publisher=[[Tulane_University_Law_School|Tulane University Law School]]|location=New Orleans|date=May 2002|url=http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=301475|format=PDF|doi=|accessdate=2010-10-12|archive-date=2010-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101212002017/http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=301475|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="CloudedBooks">{{cite news|last=Hiltzik|first=Michael A.|url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/103911266.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Jan+31%2C+2002&author=MICHAEL+A.+HILTZIK&pub=Los+Angeles+Times&edition=&startpage=A.1&desc=THE+NATION%3B+THE+FALL+OF+ENRON%3B+Enron%27s+Web+of+Complex+Hedges%2C+Bets%3B+Finances%3A+Massive+trading+of+derivatives+may+have+clouded+the+firm%27s+books%2C+experts+say.|work=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]|title=Enron's Web of Complex Hedges, Bets; Finances: Massive trading of derivatives may have clouded the firm's books, experts say|format=Fee required|date=2002-01-31|accessdate=2010-10-16|archive-date=2013-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130120073746/http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/103911266.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Jan+31%2C+2002&author=MICHAEL+A.+HILTZIK&pub=Los+Angeles+Times&edition=&startpage=A.1&desc=THE+NATION%3B+THE+FALL+OF+ENRON%3B+Enron%27s+Web+of+Complex+Hedges%2C+Bets%3B+Finances%3A+Massive+trading+of+derivatives+may+have+clouded+the+firm%27s+books%2C+experts+say.|dead-url=no}}</ref> 该特殊目的实体已被用于支付所有利用这些实体的[[债券|债务工具]] 。脚注还宣称这些工具面值总计15亿美元，而与安然的[[金融衍生工具|衍生工具合约]]显示的[[名义价值|名义价值]]为21亿美元。<ref name="DarkSide33"/>

安然为Raptors增加资本，使用的是与公司在公开发行股票时类似的会计方式，在[[资产负债表|资产负债表]]中将应付票据记作资产，同时增加相同金额的[[股东权益|股东权益]]。<ref name="DarkSide38">{{cite journal|last=Bratton|first=William W.|title=Does Corporate Law Protect the Interests of Shareholders and Other Stakeholders?: Enron and the Dark Side of Shareholder Value|journal=[[Tulane_Law_Review|Tulane Law Review]]|volume=|issue=1275|page=38|publisher=[[Tulane_University_Law_School|Tulane University Law School]]|location=New Orleans|date=May 2002|url=http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=301475|format=PDF|doi=|accessdate=2010-10-12|archive-date=2010-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101212002017/http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=301475|dead-url=no}}</ref> 这种做法后来成为安然公司和其会计师事务所[[安达信会计师事务所|安达信]]的一个问题，因为将之从资产负债表中移除会使净[[股东权益|股东权益]]减少12亿美元。<ref name="1BillionSE">{{cite news |last=Flood |first=Mary |url=http://www.chron.com/disp/story.mpl/special/enron/3657249.html |work=[[Houston_Chronicle|Houston Chronicle]] |title=Spotlight falls on Enron's crash point |date=2006-02-14 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ1jZ1Zd?url=http://www.chron.com/disp/story.mpl/special/enron/3657249.html |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

最终，这些价值21亿的衍生工具合约价值暴跌。[[掉期交易|掉期]]合约是在股价达到峰值时建立。在随后的一年里，随着股价下跌，掉期投资组合的价值下降了11亿（价值损失意味着严格来说这些特殊目的实体现在欠安然11亿美元）。安然采用了“逐日盯市”的会计方法，在其2000年的[[年报|年报]]中声称掉期合约获利5亿美元 。这些获利负责抵消其股票投资组合损失，构成了2000年安然公司盈利的近三分之一（在2001年被适当重述之前）。<ref name="DarkSide39">{{cite journal|last=Bratton|first=William W.|title=Does Corporate Law Protect the Interests of Shareholders and Other Stakeholders?: Enron and the Dark Side of Shareholder Value|journal=[[Tulane_Law_Review|Tulane Law Review]]|volume=|issue=1275|page=39|publisher=[[Tulane_University_Law_School|Tulane University Law School]]|location=New Orleans|date=May 2002|url=http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=301475|format=PDF|doi=|accessdate=2010-10-12|archive-date=2010-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101212002017/http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=301475|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 企业管治 ===
理论上，安然拥有主要由持有大量股份的外部人士构成的堪称典范的[[董事会|董事会]]以及才能卓著的审计委员会。在评价2000年企业最佳董事会时，《首席执行官》 （Chief Executive）杂志将安然列入前五名。<ref name="Gillan21">{{cite journal|last=Gillan|first=Stuart|author2=John D. Martin|title=Financial Engineering, Corporate Governance, and the Collapse of Enron|page=21|publisher=[[Alfred_Lerner_College_of_Business_and_Economics,_The_University_of_Delaware|Alfred Lerner College of Business and Economics, The University of Delaware]]|date=November 2002|url=http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=354040|doi=|accessdate=2010-10-16|journal=|archive-date=2012-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120111050729/http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=354040|dead-url=no}}</ref> 即使拥有复杂的公司治理和中间人网络，安然仍能“吸引大笔资金为可疑的商业模式融资，通过一系列的会计和金融手段隐瞒其真实表现，将股价炒作到无法维持的高位。”<ref name="Healy4">{{cite journal |last=Healy |first=Paul M. |author2=Krishna G. Palepu |title=The Fall of Enron |journal=[[Journal_of_Economic_Perspectives|Journal of Economic Perspectives]] |volume=17 |issue=2 |page=4 |date=Spring 2003 |url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf |format=PDF |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0YEF6T?url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf |archivedate=2010-10-18 |doi=10.1257/089533003765888403 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

==== 高管薪酬 ====
虽然安然公司的薪酬和绩效管理体系意在保留和奖励其最有价值的员工，但该系统导致了不正常的[[企业文化|企业文化]]，即看重短期盈利以最大化奖金。员工不断试图进行交易，往往忽视现金流或利润的质量，为的是在绩效考核中获得更好的评级。此外，会计结果被尽可能快地记录以跟上公司股价。这种做法有助于确保交易的决策者和管理人员获得大量的现金红利和股票期权。<ref name="DharanRed1120">{{cite journal |last=Dharan |first=Bala G. |author2=William R. Bufkins |title=Red Flags in Enron's Reporting of Revenues and Key Financial Measures |page=112 |publisher=Social Science Research Network |date=July 2008 |url=http://www.ruf.rice.edu/~bala/files/dharan-bufkins_enron_red_flags.pdf |doi= |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0yCA9i?url=http://www.ruf.rice.edu/~bala/files/dharan-bufkins_enron_red_flags.pdf |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes |journal= }}</ref>

该公司不断强调其股价。管理层广泛通过股票[[期权|期权]]获得酬劳，与其他美国公司类似。这种股票期权奖励政策导致管理层努力创造报告收益呈现迅速增长的预期以符合华尔街的预期。这支股票的代码在大堂、电梯和公司电脑上随处可见。<ref name="McLean187">{{cite book|title=The Smartest Guys in the Room|year=2003|url=https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle|last=McLean|first=Bethany|author2=Peter Elkind|page=[https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle/page/187 187]|isbn=1-59184-008-2}}</ref> 预算会议上，斯基林制定目标收益时会问“你需要多少收益来保持我们的股价上涨？”，然后那个数字会被采用，即使它是不可行的。<ref name="McLean127"/> 在2000年12月31日，安然有9600万股流通股作为股票期权计划（占全部流通股的约13%）。安然的股东委托书中表示，三年内这些奖励都有望得到执行。<ref name="Healy13">{{cite journal |last=Healy |first=Paul M. |author2=Krishna G. Palepu |title=The Fall of Enron |journal=[[Journal_of_Economic_Perspectives|Journal of Economic Perspectives]] |volume=17 |issue=2 |page=13 |date=Spring 2003 |url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf |format=PDF |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0YEF6T?url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf |archivedate=2010-10-18 |doi=10.1257/089533003765888403 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 以2001年1月的安然股价83.13美元和2001年股东委托书中报告的董事会受益所有权计算，Lay的董事持股价值是6.59亿美元，斯基林是1.74亿美元。<ref name="Gillan21"/>

斯基林认为如果员工们经常担心成本会妨碍创新思维。<ref name="McLean119">{{cite book|title=The Smartest Guys in the Room|year=2003|url=https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle|last=McLean|first=Bethany|author2=Peter Elkind|page=[https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle/page/119 119]|isbn=1-59184-008-2}}</ref> 结果，奢侈消费弥漫整个公司，尤其高管们。员工们有大笔的开支账目和许多高管有时支付两倍于竞争对手的价格。<ref name="McLean401">{{cite book|title=The Smartest Guys in the Room|year=2003|url=https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle|last=McLean|first=Bethany|author2=Peter Elkind|page=[https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle/page/401 401]|isbn=1-59184-008-2}}</ref> 1998年前200名收入最高的员工收到工资、奖金和股票总计1.93亿美元。两年后这一数字跃升至14亿。<ref name="McLean241">{{cite book|title=The Smartest Guys in the Room|year=2003|url=https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle|last=McLean|first=Bethany|author2=Peter Elkind|page=[https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle/page/241 241]|isbn=1-59184-008-2}}</ref>

==== 风险管理 ====
在丑闻之前，安然因其复杂精致的[[金融风险管理|金融风险管理]]工具备受赞誉。<ref name="DynamicFT">{{cite news |last=Kim |first=W. Chan |author2=Renée Mauborgne |url=http://knowledge.insead.edu/abstract.cfm?ct=6973 |work=[[Financial_Times|Financial Times]] |title=New dynamics of strategy in the knowledge economy |date=1999-10-11 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ1oZnXs?url=http://knowledge.insead.edu/abstract.cfm?ct=6973 |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 风险管理对于安然至关重要不仅由于其监管环境，也因为其业务计划 。安然公司负有长期固定的支付款项，需要加以对冲，为未来能源价格的持续波动做好准备。<ref name="Rosen1171">{{cite journal|last=Rosen|first=Robert|title=Risk Management and Corporate Governance: The Case of Enron|journal=[[Connecticut_Law_Review|Connecticut Law Review]]|volume=35|issue=1157|page=1171|publisher=|location=|year=2003|url=http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=468168|doi=|accessdate=2010-10-16|archive-date=2012-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120111052503/http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=468168|dead-url=no}}</ref> 安然公司的破产崩溃可以归结于其对衍生品和特殊目的实体的轻率使用。虽然与它拥有的特殊目的实体对冲了风险，安然依旧承担着与交易相关的风险。这种安排相当于安然与其自身对冲风险。<ref name="Rosen1171">{{cite journal|last=Rosen|first=Robert|title=Risk Management and Corporate Governance: The Case of Enron|journal=[[Connecticut_Law_Review|Connecticut Law Review]]|volume=35|issue=1157|page=1171|publisher=|location=|year=2003|url=http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=468168|doi=|accessdate=2010-10-16}}</ref>

安然激进的会计操作没有瞒过董事会，后来又被一个参议院小组委员会发现。董事会知悉使用 Whitewing，LJM 和 Raptor 交易的根据，并在批准他们之后收到了这些实体运作状态的最新消息。虽然不是所有安然的广泛使用的不当会计行为都为董事会所知，但这些做法都依靠董事会的决策。<ref name="Rosen1170">{{cite journal|last=Rosen|first=Robert|title=Risk Management and Corporate Governance: The Case of Enron|journal=[[Connecticut_Law_Review|Connecticut Law Review]]|volume=35|issue=1157|page=1170|publisher=|location=|year=2003|url=http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=468168|doi=|accessdate=2010-10-16|archive-date=2012-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120111052503/http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=468168|dead-url=no}}</ref> 尽管安然的业务广泛依赖衍生品，公司的财务委员会和董事会也没有足够衍生品相关经验来理解他们被告知的内容。参议院小组委员会认为，如果对这些衍生品如何组织有充分了解，董事会本来能够阻止其使用。<ref name="Rosen1175">{{cite journal|last=Rosen|first=Robert|title=Risk Management and Corporate Governance: The Case of Enron|journal=[[Connecticut_Law_Review|Connecticut Law Review]]|volume=35|issue=1157|page=1175|publisher=|location=|year=2003|url=http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=468168|doi=|accessdate=2010-10-16|archive-date=2012-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120111052503/http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=468168|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==== 财务审计 ====
安然公司的[[会计|会计]]师事务所[[安达信|安达信]]被指控在审计中应用轻率的标准，这是由安然支付的巨额咨询费带来的[[利益冲突|利益冲突]]所致。2000年，安达信获得了2500万美元的审计费用和2700万美元的咨询费用（该金额占安达信[[休斯敦|休斯敦]]办事处公众客户审计费用的约27％）。会计师的方法遭到质疑，既是因为单单收取年费就算完成审计，也是由于其缺乏适当审查安然的收入确认、特殊实体、衍生品和其他会计实务的专业知识。<ref name="Healy15">{{cite journal |last=Healy |first=Paul M. |author2=Krishna G. Palepu |title=The Fall of Enron |journal=[[Journal_of_Economic_Perspectives|Journal of Economic Perspectives]] |volume=17 |issue=2 |page=15 |date=Spring 2003 |url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf |format=PDF |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0YEF6T?url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf |archivedate=2010-10-18 |doi=10.1257/089533003765888403 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

安然公司聘请了众多的注册会计师 （Certified Public Accountants，CPAs），以及曾与财务会计准则委员会（Financial Accounting Standards Board，FASB）一起编写会计规则的会计师。会计师寻找新的方式为公司节省开支，包括利用一般公认会计原则（Generally Accepted Accounting Principles，GAAP）中的漏洞。一位安然的会计师透露“我们积极地尝试利用这份文献[GAAP]来获利。所有规则都创造这种机会。我们落到如此境地是因为我们利用了这些缺陷。”<ref name="McLean142">{{cite book|title=The Smartest Guys in the Room|year=2003|url=https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle|last=McLean|first=Bethany|author2=Peter Elkind|page=[https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle/page/142 142]|isbn=1-59184-008-2}}</ref>

安达信的会计师受到安然管理层施加的压力，推迟确认来自特殊目的实体的费用，这些实体因其[[信用风险|信用风险]]为人所知。由于这些实体无法赢利，会计准则要求安然应该采取注销，即从资产负债表中移除处于亏损的实体的价值。为了对安达信施压使其满足安然公司的盈利预期，安然偶尔会让[[安永|安永]]会计师事务所或[[普华永道|普华永道]]完成会计任务，以创造雇用新的公司取代安达信的错觉。<ref name="McLean148">{{cite book|title=The Smartest Guys in the Room|year=2003|url=https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle|last=McLean|first=Bethany|author2=Peter Elkind|page=[https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle/page/148 148]|isbn=1-59184-008-2}}</ref> 虽然安达信具备内部控制以防止本地合作伙伴的冲突激励，但它未能防止利益冲突。在一个案例中，为安然审计的安达信休斯敦办事处能够否决安达信芝加哥合伙人对安然会计决策的任何关键评论。此外，[[美国证券交易委员会|美国证券交易委员会]]（SEC）调查安然公司的消息公开之后，安达信粉碎了数吨有关文件，并删除近3万封电子邮件和计算机文件，导致其被控掩盖罪行。<ref name="Healy15"/><ref name="DVD132">{{cite video|title=[[Enron:_The_Smartest_Guys_in_the_Room|Enron: The Smartest Guys in the Room]]|medium=DVD|publisher=[[Magnolia_Pictures|Magnolia Pictures]]|time=1:32:33|date=January 17, 2006}}</ref><ref name="McLean383">{{cite book|title=The Smartest Guys in the Room|year=2003|url=https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle|last=McLean|first=Bethany|author2=Peter Elkind|page=[https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle/page/383 383]|isbn=1-59184-008-2}}</ref>

对安达信总体表现的揭露导致其解体，权力委员会（2001年10月由安然公司董事会任命，调查该公司的会计）作出下述评价：“我们获得的证据表明，安达信没有履行与安然财务报表审计相关的职责，也没有尽到使安然董事会（或审计与合规委员会）关注安然内部关联交易合约的义务。”<ref name="Cornford30">{{cite journal |last=Cornford |first=Andrew |title=Internationally Agreed Principles For Corporate Governance And The Enron Case |journal=G-24 Discussion Paper Series No. 30 |page=30 |publisher=[[United_Nations_Conference_on_Trade_and_Development|United Nations Conference on Trade and Development]] |location=New York |date=June 2004 |url=http://www.unctad.org/en/docs/gdsmdpbg2420046_en.pdf |format=PDF |doi= |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ1KQjhV?url=http://www.unctad.org/en/docs/gdsmdpbg2420046_en.pdf |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

==== 审计委员会 ====
企业审计委员会一年通常只开几次会，他们的成员一般只有极少的会计和财务经验。安然公司的审计委员会拥有的专业知识远超过其他很多公司。它包括：<ref name="AuditComitMembers">{{cite news|last=Lublin|first=Joann S.|url=http://bodurtha.georgetown.edu/enron/Enron%20Audit%20Panel%20Is%20Scrutinized%20For%20Its%20Cozy%20Ties%20With%20the%20Firm.htm|work=The Wall Street Journal|title=Enron Audit Panel Is Scrutinized For Its Cozy Ties With the Firm|date=2002-02-01|accessdate=2009-08-09|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20121214180037/http://bodurtha.georgetown.edu/enron/Enron%20Audit%20Panel%20Is%20Scrutinized%20For%20Its%20Cozy%20Ties%20With%20the%20Firm.htm|archivedate=2012-12-14}}</ref>
*Robert Jaedicke，一位广受尊敬的会计学教授和[[斯坦福大学|斯坦福大学]]商学院前院长
*John Mendelsohn，德克萨斯大学 M.D.安德森癌症中心主席
*Paulo Pereira，巴西里约热内卢国家银行前总裁兼首席执行官
*John Wakeham，前英国能源部长
*[[陳啟宗|陳啟宗]]，[[香港|香港]][[恒隆集團|恒隆集團]]董事長
*Wendy Gramm，美国[[商品期货交易委员会|商品期货交易委员会]]（Commodity Futures Trading Commission）前主席

安然公司的审计委员会后来因为召开覆盖大量内容的简短会议而受到批评。在2001年2月12日一次会议中，该委员会的会面持续了一个半小时。安然的审计委员会在特殊目的实体的会计问题方面没有足够的技术知识来恰当地质疑会计师。该委员会由于受到压力也未能质疑公司管理层。<ref name="Healy14">{{cite journal |last=Healy |first=Paul M. |author2=Krishna G. Palepu |title=The Fall of Enron |journal=[[Journal_of_Economic_Perspectives|Journal of Economic Perspectives]] |volume=17 |issue=2 |page=14 |date=Spring 2003 |url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf |format=PDF |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ0YEF6T?url=http://www-personal.umich.edu/~kathrynd/JEP.FallofEnron.pdf |archivedate=2010-10-18 |doi=10.1257/089533003765888403 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 美国参议院常设小组委员会关于政府事务委员会的调查报告指责董事会成员允许利益冲突妨碍其监控公司会计惯例的职责。安然的丑闻东窗事发时，审计委员会被认为有利益冲突之嫌。<ref name="Deakin9">{{cite journal |last=Deakin |first=Simon |author2=Suzanne J. Konzelmann |title=Learning from Enron |journal=ESRC Centre for Business Research |volume= |issue=Working Paper No 274 |page=9 |publisher=[[University_of_Cambridge|University of Cambridge]] |date=September 2003 |url=http://www.cbr.cam.ac.uk/pdf/wp274.pdf |format=PDF |doi= |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ21BvjA?url=http://www.cbr.cam.ac.uk/pdf/wp274.pdf |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

==== 伦理和政治分析 ====
评论家将安然公司崩溃背后的管理不善归咎于各种各样伦理与政治经济原因。伦理学上的解释集中于高管的贪婪和傲慢，缺乏企业社会责任，情境伦理学，和“把事办成”（get-it-done）的商业实用主义。<ref>Kristen Hayes, "Executives’ greed big factor in Enron crash, probe shows" ''The Seattle Times, ''August 23, 2002.</ref><ref>Bethany McLean, “Why Enron Went Bust: Start with Arrogance,” ''Fortune'', December 24, 2001.</ref><ref>Duane Windsor, “Business Ethics at ‘The Crooked E’” in ''Enron: Corporate Fiascos and Legal Implications'', ed. Nanacy Rapoport and Bala Dharan, 659—87. New York: Foundation Press, 2004.</ref><ref>Alan Charles Raul, “In Era of Broken Rules, Society Breaks,” ''Los Angeles Times'', October 11, 2002</ref><ref>“Enron: Whatever happened to risk management?” ''Personnel Today'', March 19, 2002.</ref> 政治经济学解释归咎于1970年代后的放松管制，用于管理机构监督的人员和资金不足。<ref>David Leonhardt, “How Will Washington Read the Signs?” ''The New York Times'', February 10, 2002.</ref><ref>Staff of the Committee on Governmental Affairs, United States Senate, “Financial Oversight of Enron: The SEC and the Private-Sector Watchdogs,” October 7, 2002.</ref> 更为自由意志主义的分析认为，安然公司的崩溃源于其对政治游说、[[寻租|寻租]]和法规博弈的依赖。 <ref>Robert L. Bradley Jr., "Enron: The Perils of Interventionism", Library of Economics and Liberty</ref>

=== 其它会计问题 ===
安然公司习惯于将取消项目的成本作为资产记录，根据是没有公函宣布过该项目已被取消。这种方法被称为“雪球”，虽然最初规定这种做法只能用于价值低于9000万美元的项目，但后来增加到2亿。<ref name="McLean77">{{cite book|title=The Smartest Guys in the Room|year=2003|url=https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle|last=McLean|first=Bethany|author2=Peter Elkind|page=[https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle/page/77 77]|isbn=1-59184-008-2}}</ref>

1998年，当分析师们参观安然能源服务办公室时，他们对员工工作之积极活跃印象深刻。实际上，斯基林把其他部门的员工转移到这间办公室（指示他们假装努力工作）以使该部门的规模看起来更大一些。<ref name="McLean1798">{{cite book|title=The Smartest Guys in the Room|year=2003|url=https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle|last=McLean|first=Bethany|author2=Peter Elkind|pages=[https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle/page/179 179]–180|isbn=1-59184-008-2}}</ref> 这个诡计被多次使用，愚弄研究安然不同领域的进展情况的分析师，以提升股价。

