2002年1月17日，安然解雇了其审计师的安达信，理由是其会计建议和对文件的销毁。安达信反驳说，安然破产时它与这家公司的关系就结束了。<ref name="FiresAA">{{cite news |last=DeVogue |first=Ariane |author2=Peter Dizikes |author3=Linda Douglass |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Business/story?id=87413&page=1 |title=Enron Fires Arthur Andersen |publisher=[[ABC_News|ABC News]] |date=2002-01-18 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ4YrFj8?url=http://abcnews.go.com/Business/story?id=87413 |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

== 审判 ==

=== 安然 ===
法斯托与妻子Lea都对指控认罪。法斯托最初被控98项欺诈、[[洗钱|洗钱]]、[[内幕交易|内幕交易]]和共谋及其他罪行。<ref name="Fastow98">{{cite news |agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] |url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB113838648001558434.html?mod=googlewsj |title=Key Witnesses in the Enron Trial |work=[[The_Wall_Street_Journal|The Wall Street Journal]] |format=Fee required |date=2006-01-27 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ4bV4PY?url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB113838648001558434.html?mod=googlewsj |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 法斯托对两项共谋指控认罪，被判十年监禁不得假释，在[[认罪协商|认罪协商]]中作证起诉莱、斯基林和考西。 <ref name="FastowTestify">{{cite news |last=Said |first=Carolyn |url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?file=/c/a/2004/07/09/MNGQQ7J31G1.DTL |title=Ex-Enron chief Ken Lay Enters Not Guilty Plea |work=[[San_Francisco_Chronicle|San Francisco Chronicle]] |date=2004-07-09 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ4eDgmv?url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?file=%2Fc%2Fa%2F2004%2F07%2F09%2FMNGQQ7J31G1.DTL |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> Lea被起诉6项重罪，但检察官后来撤销了这些重罪，取而代之的是一项税收指控的轻罪。Lea因帮助丈夫向政府隐瞒收入被判一年监禁。<ref name="LeaYear">{{cite news |last=Hays |first=Kristen |url=http://www.usatoday.com/money/industries/energy/2004-05-06-lea-fastow-plea_x.htm |title=Fastow's Wife Pleads Guilty in Enron Case |work=[[USA_Today|USA Today]] |date=2004-05-06 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ4f0B1f?url=http://www.usatoday.com/money/industries/energy/2004-05-06-lea-fastow-plea_x.htm |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

莱和斯基林在2006年1月为他们在安然丑闻中的作用受审。这份65页的起诉书有53项罪名，涵盖广泛的金融犯罪，包括银行欺诈、对银行和审计师作出虚假陈述、证券欺诈、电信欺诈、洗钱、共谋和内幕交易。美国[[地方法院|地方法院]]法官希姆•雷克（Sim Lake）拒绝被告提出的分别审理和在休斯顿之外审理的要求，被告辩称安然破产在休斯顿的负面报道使此地难以进行公正的审判。2006年5月25日，莱和斯基林审判的陪审团做出裁决。斯基林被裁定28项指控中的19项证券欺诈和电信欺诈罪名成立，其余9项内幕交易罪被判无罪。他被判24年4个月的监禁。<ref name="Skilling24Years">{{cite news |last=Johnson |first=Carrie |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/10/23/AR2006102300287_pf.html |work=[[Washington_Post|Washington Post]] |title=Skilling Gets 24 Years for Fraud at Enron |date=2006-10-24 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ4meIIM?url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/10/23/AR2006102300287_pf.html |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 2013年美国司法部与斯基林达成协议，使其刑期减少10年。<ref name="JeffSkilling Resentencing">{{cite web|title=Ex-Enron Chief's Sentence is Cut by 10 Years to 14|url=http://dealbook.nytimes.com/2013/06/21/prison-sentence-of-ex-enron-ceo-skilling-cut-by-10-years-2/|accessdate=2013-06-21|publisher=’''The New York Times''’|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112024324/https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2013/06/21/prison-sentence-of-ex-enron-ceo-skilling-cut-by-10-years-2|dead-url=no}}</ref>

莱不承认11项刑事指控，并声称他是被周围的人所误导。他将公司破产归咎于法斯托。<ref name="Lay60Minutes">{{cite news |last=Leung |first=Rebecca |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2005/03/11/60minutes/main679706.shtml |work=[[60_Minutes|60 Minutes]] |publisher=[[CBS_News|CBS News]] |title=Enron's Ken Lay: I Was Fooled |date=2005-03-14 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ4onkPe?url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2005/03/11/60minutes/main679706.shtml |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 莱被指控的6项证券和电信欺诈罪全部成立，被判处总计入狱45年的最高刑期。 <ref name="Lay45Years">{{cite news |last=Hays |first=Kristen |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/05/25/AR2006052500857.html |work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]] |title=Lay, Skilling Convicted in Enron Collapse |date=2006-05-26 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ4oyTyi?url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/05/25/AR2006052500857.html |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 然而莱在宣判日前的2006年7月5日死去。莱死时SEC还在寻求向他追加超过9000万的民事罚款。莱的妻子琳达（Linda）的案子比较困难。2001年11月28日她在安然崩溃的消息公开前的10到30分钟，卖出大约50万股的安然股票。<ref name="EnronInquiryNYT">{{cite news |last=Eichenwald |first=Kurt |url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9806EED8123FF934A25752C1A9629C8B63&sec=&spon= |work=The New York Times |title=Enron Inquiry Turns to Sales By Lay's Wife |date=2004-11-17 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ4t79Jq?url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9806EED8123FF934A25752C1A9629C8B63 |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 琳达从未被控任何与安然有关的事件。 <ref name="LindaConviction">{{cite news |last=Johnson |first=Carrie |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/06/09/AR2006060901922_pf.html |work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]] |title=A Woman Of Conviction |date=2006-06-10 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ4vdFd0?url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/06/09/AR2006060901922_pf.html |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

虽然迈克尔·科珀（Michael Kopper）曾在安然工作超过七年，莱甚至在公司破产之后都不知道科珀。科珀在整个事件中保持匿名。<ref name="McLean153">{{cite book|title=The Smartest Guys in the Room|year=2003|url=https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle|last=McLean|first=Bethany|author2=Peter Elkind|page=[https://archive.org/details/smartestguysin00mcle/page/153 153]|isbn=1-59184-008-2}}</ref> 科珀是安然第一个认罪的高管。<ref name="KopperGuilty">{{cite news |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/2002/aug/21/corporatefraud.enron1 |publisher=[[guardian.co.uk|guardian.co.uk]] |title=Ex-Enron executive pleads guilty |location=London |date=2002-08-21 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ4xrCBl?url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/2002/aug/21/corporatefraud.enron1 |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 首席会计官里克·考西因在任职期间隐瞒安然财务状况的被控6项重罪。<ref name="Causey6Charges">{{cite news |last=Ackman |first=Dan |url=http://www.forbes.com/2004/01/23/cx_da_0123topnewse.html |work=[[Forbes_(magazine)|Forbes]] |title=Causey May Put GAAP On Trial |date=2004-01-23 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ51WZVb?url=http://www.forbes.com/2004/01/23/cx_da_0123topnewse.html |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 他起初不承认控罪，后来认罪被判入狱7年。<ref name="Causey7Years">{{cite news |last=McCoy |first=Kevin |url=http://www.usatoday.com/money/industries/energy/2005-12-28-enron-causey_x.htm?POE=NEWISVA |work=[[USA_Today|USA Today]] |title=Former Enron executive pleads guilty |date=2005-12-28 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ53FHwX?url=http://www.usatoday.com/money/industries/energy/2005-12-28-enron-causey_x.htm?POE=NEWISVA |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

总而言之，16人承认在公司所犯的罪行。另外5人被判有罪，包括四名前[[美林证券|美林证券]]雇员。8名安然前高管作证——主要证人是法斯托——指控他们的前老板莱和斯基林。 <ref name="DayReckonCNN"/> 肯尼思·赖斯（Kenneth Rice），安然公司高速互联网部门的前主管，合作并作证协助为斯基林和莱定罪。2007年6月，他获判27个月刑期。<ref name="BroadSentence">{{cite news |last=Porretto |first=John |url=http://www.usatoday.com/money/economy/2007-06-18-3270186548_x.htm |title=Ex-Enron broadband head sentenced |work=[[USA_Today|USA Today]] |date=2007-06-18 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ554fEd?url=http://www.usatoday.com/money/economy/2007-06-18-3270186548_x.htm |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

迈克尔·W·克劳兹（Michael W. Krautz），前安然公司会计，是相关丑闻指控所有被告中唯一被判无罪的。<ref>{{cite web|last=Murphy|first=Kate|title=One Guilty and One Acquitted in Enron Broadband Trial|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/06/01/business/businessspecial3/01enron.html|publisher=The New York Times|access-date=2016-02-19|archive-date=2020-11-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201121050256/https://www.nytimes.com/2006/06/01/business/businessspecial3/01enron.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 巴里·波拉克（Barry Pollack）为其辩护，<ref>{{cite web|last=Ellison|first=Cara|title=Michael Krautz: Sexy Accountant|url=http://caraellison.wordpress.com/2010/06/17/michael-krautz-sexy-accountant/|publisher=The Enron Blog|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120709024836/http://caraellison.wordpress.com/2010/06/17/michael-krautz-sexy-accountant/|archivedate=2012-07-09|access-date=2016-02-19}}</ref> 长达一个月的陪审团审判后，克劳兹的联邦刑事欺诈指控罪名不成立。

=== 安达信 ===
安达信因撕毁数千份文件及删除电子邮件和有关安然会计业务的公司文件被指控妨碍司法公正，并被判有罪。<ref name="AndersenGuilty">{{cite news |last=Thomas |first=Cathy Booth |title=Called to Account |url=http://www.time.com/time/business/article/0,8599,263006,00.html |date=2002-06-18 |work=[[Time_(magazine)|Time]] |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ56HIkr?url=http://www.time.com/time/business/article/0,8599,263006,00.html |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 虽然只有少数安达信员工涉及这一丑闻，该公司依然停业；SEC不会承认被判有罪的重罪犯进行的审计。该公司2002年8月31日放弃了注册会计师执照，8.5万名员工失去工作。<ref name="WP85000Jobs">{{cite news |last=Rosenwald |first=Michael S. |title=Extreme (Executive) Makeover |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/09/09/AR2007090901619_pf.html |date=2007-11-10 |work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]] |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5E2wBX?url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/09/09/AR2007090901619_pf.html |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref name="FallAndersen">{{cite news |last=Alexander |first=Delroy |author2=Greg Burns |author3=Robert Manor |author4=Flynn McRoberts |author5=and E.A. Torriero |title=The Fall of Andersen |url=http://www.courant.com/news/nationworld/chi-0209010315sep01,0,2343149.story |date=2002-11-01 |work=[[Hartford_Courant|Hartford Courant]] |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5GUhP8?url=http://www.courant.com/news/nation-world/chi-0209010315sep01,0,6548944.story |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 这一判决后来被[[美国最高法院|美国最高法院]]推翻，原因是在对安达信的指控中陪审团没有获得正确的说明。<ref name="AndersenOverturn">{{cite news |agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] |title=Supreme Court Overturns Arthur Andersen Conviction |url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,158160,00.html |date=2005-05-31 |publisher=[[Fox_News_Channel|Fox News]] |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5BkNtb?url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,158160,00.html |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 最高法院的裁决理论上使安达信可以恢复运营。但是安达信的名声受损过于严重，以致于甚至无法在有限范围内恢复可行的业务。

=== 国民威斯敏斯特银行的三人 ===
贾尔斯·达比（Giles Darby）、大卫·伯明翰（David Bermingham）和加里·马尔格鲁（Gary Mulgrew）为[[国民威斯敏斯特银行|国民威斯敏斯特银行]]工作。这3名英国人和法斯托一起在其创立的特殊目的实体工作，这些实体被称为掉期替身（Swap Sub）。当法斯托正被SEC调查时，这三个人2001年11月与[[英国金融服务管理局|英国金融服务管理局]]（Financial Services Authority，FSA）讨论了他们和法斯托的合作。<ref name="FSAMet">{{cite news |last=Hays |first=Kristen |work=[[Houston_Chronicle|Houston Chronicle]] |title=Source: British bankers to plead guilty in Enron case |url=http://www.chron.com/disp/story.mpl/special/enron/5333449.html |date=2007-11-27 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5Joi5a?url=http://www.chron.com/disp/story.mpl/business/energy/5333449.html |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 2002年6月，美国因7项电信欺诈罪对他们发出逮捕令，后将其引渡。7月12日，一位原定被引渡到美国的证人尼尔·库尔贝克（Neil Coulbeck）被发现死在伦敦东北部的一个公园。<ref name="CoulbeckDead">{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/5173228.stm |publisher=BBC News |title=Enron Witness Found Dead in Park |date=2006-07-12 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5Ly1MZ?url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/5173228.stm |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 库尔贝克的死亡最终被裁定为自杀。<ref name="CoulbeckSuicide">{{cite web |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-457212/NatWest-Three-bankers-suicide-park.html |title=NatWest Three banker's suicide in the park |publisher=Dailymail.co.uk |date=2007-05-23 |accessdate=2013-09-02 |archive-date=2020-11-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201123194848/https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-457212/NatWest-Three-bankers-suicide-park.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 美国的案件认为，库尔贝克和其他人与法斯托合谋。 <ref name="CoulbeckQA">{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/business/5164652.stm |publisher=BBC News |title=Q&A: The NatWest Three |date=2007-11-29 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5PESnK?url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/business/5164652.stm |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 在2007年11月的认罪协议中，三人承认电信欺诈的罪名，而其余6项指控被驳回。<ref name="Trio7Fraud">{{cite news |last=Clark |first=Andrew |publisher=[[guardian.co.uk|guardian.co.uk]] |title=NatWest Three Plead Guilty to Wire Fraud |location=London |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/2007/nov/28/2 |date=2007-11-28 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5RoiUC?url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/business/2007/nov/28/2 |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 达比、伯明翰和穆尔格鲁分别被判有期徒刑37个月。<ref name="NatWest3NYT">{{cite news |last=Murphy |first=Kate |work=The New York Times |title='NatWest 3' sentenced to 37 months each |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/02/22/business/worldbusiness/22iht-natwest.5.10317714.html?_r=2 |date=2008-02-22 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5RcYaO?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/02/22/business/worldbusiness/22iht-natwest.5.10317714.html?_r=3 |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 2010年8月，伯明翰和马尔格鲁撤回了他们的供词。<ref name="TortureDT">{{cite news |last=Tyler |first=Richard |work=[[Daily_Telegraph|Daily Telegraph]] |title=NatWest banker claims he was 'tortured' into pleading guilty over theft of $7.3m from RBS |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/banksandfinance/7947139/NatWest-banker-claims-he-was-tortured-into-pleading-guilty-over-theft-of-7.3m-from-RBS.html |date=2010-08-15 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5WJSP6?url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/banksandfinance/7947139/NatWest-banker-claims-he-was-tortured-into-pleading-guilty-over-theft-of-7.3m-from-RBS.html |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

== 余波 == 

=== 员工与股东 ===
[[File:Enron_Complex.jpg|thumb]]

安然公司的股东在公司破产前的四年内损失了740亿美元（其中400至450亿是因为欺诈）。<ref name="74BEnron">{{cite news |last=Axtman |first=Kris |title=How Enron awards do, or don't, trickle down |url=http://www.csmonitor.com/2005/0620/p02s01-usju.html |work=[[The_Christian_Science_Monitor|The Christian Science Monitor]] |date=2005-06-20 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5aLijg?url=http://www.csmonitor.com/2005/0620/p02s01-usju.html |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 由于安然欠债权人近670亿美元，员工和股东除了遣散费外只收到了有限的援助，如果有的话。<ref name="67BillionNYT">{{cite news |title=Enron's Plan Would Repay A Fraction of Dollars Owed |work=The New York Times |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2003/07/12/business/enron-s-plan-would-repay-a-fraction-of-dollars-owed.html |date=2003-07-12 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5cPyj6?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2003/07/12/business/enron-s-plan-would-repay-a-fraction-of-dollars-owed.html |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 为了偿还债务，安然拍卖资产，包括艺术品、照片、logo标志和其管道。<ref name="ArtNYT">{{cite news |last=Vogel |first=Carol |title=Enron's Art to Be Auctioned Off |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2003/04/16/business/enron-s-art-to-be-auctioned-off.html |date=2003-04-16 |work=The New York Times |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5cZwye?url=http://www.nytimes.com/2003/04/16/business/enron-s-art-to-be-auctioned-off.html |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref name="TiltedE">{{cite news |agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]] |title=Enron's 'Tilted-E' Sign Goes for $44,000 at Auction |url=http://www.usatoday.com/money/industries/energy/2002-09-25-enron-auction_x.htm |date=2002-09-25 |work=[[USA_Today|USA Today]] |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5gVrx2?url=http://www.usatoday.com/money/industries/energy/2002-09-25-enron-auction_x.htm |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref name="SellPipes">{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/business/3646342.stm |title=Enron Gets Go Ahead to Sell Pipes |date=2004-09-10 |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5iipwI?url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/business/3646342.stm |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

2004年5月，2万多名安然前雇员在一场诉讼中获胜，赢得了8500万美元以补偿20亿的养老金损失。根据和解协议，每名员工获赔3100美元。<ref name="May04Settlement">{{cite news |last=Doran |first=James |url=http://business.timesonline.co.uk/tol/business/article423518.ece |title=Enron Staff win $85m |location=London |date=2004-05-14 |work=[[The_Times|The Times]] |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5myXGx?url=http://business.timesonline.co.uk/tol/business/article423518.ece |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 翌年投资者与几家银行达成和解获赔42亿美元。<ref name="74BEnron"/> 2008年9月，股东们要求赔偿400亿的诉讼达成72亿美元的和解协议。赔偿在主要原告加州大学（University of California，UC）和150万个个人和团体之间分配。加州大学的律师事务所Coughlin Stoia Geller Rudman and Robbins 获得了6.88亿的费用，这是美国证券欺诈案中最高的。<ref name="72BillionSet">{{cite news |last=DeBare |first=Ilana |work=[[San_Francisco_Chronicle|San Francisco Chronicle]] |url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2008/09/09/BUCI12QRVE.DTL |title=Billions to be shared by Enron shareholders |date=2008-09-10 |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5ptOY5?url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=%2Fc%2Fa%2F2008%2F09%2F09%2FBUCI12QRVE.DTL |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 关于赔偿分配，加州大学在一份新闻稿中宣布：“我们非常高兴将这些资金返还给成员们。达成目的需要漫长且具有挑战性的努力，但结果对于安然投资者来说是前所未有的。”<ref name="Distribution">{{cite news |last=Davis |first=Trey |url=http://www.universityofcalifornia.edu/news/article/19211 |title=UC begins distributing Enron settlement money |date=2008-12-18 |publisher=[[University_of_California|University of California]] |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5tTGlZ?url=http://www.universityofcalifornia.edu/news/article/19211 |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

=== 萨班斯-奥克斯利法案 ===
{{Quote box
|width=35%
|align=right
|quote=泰坦尼克号中，船长与船同沉。安然在我看来就像是先给自己和朋友们奖金，然后把自己和高层的伙计们降到救生艇上，然后喊了一声：“对了，一切都会好起来的。”
|source=[[美国参议院|美国参议院]]议员 拜伦·多根（Byron Dorgan）。<ref name="DVD606">{{cite video|title=Enron: The Smartest Guys in the Room|medium=DVD|publisher=[[Magnolia_Pictures|Magnolia Pictures]]|time=6:06|date=January 17, 2006}}</ref>
}}
{{Main|萨班斯-奥克斯利法案}}
2001年12月至2002年4月间，参议院银行、住房和城市事务委员会（Senate Committee on Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs）和众议院金融服务委员会（House Committee on Financial Services）举行了多次有关安然丑闻以及相关会计和投资者保护问题的听证。这些听证和随后的安然公司丑闻使萨班斯-奥克斯利法案于2002年7月30日通过。<ref name="Chhaochharia79">{{cite journal |last=Chhaochharia |first=Vidhi |author2=Yaniv Grinstein |title=Corporate Governance and Firm Value: the Impact of the 2002 Governance Rules |journal=Johnson School Research Paper Series No. 23-06 |pages=7–9 |publisher=[[Johnson_School_of_Management|Johnson School of Management]] |date=March 2007 |url=http://www.afajof.org/afa/forthcoming/2312.pdf |format=PDF |doi= |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ5wCYTh?url=http://www.afajof.org/afa/forthcoming/2312.pdf |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref> 该法案几乎是“安然的镜像：这家公司明显治理失败几乎是一点对一点地与该法的主要条款相吻合。”<ref name="Deakin1">{{cite journal |last=Deakin |first=Simon |author2=Suzanne J. Konzelmann |title=Learning from Enron |journal=ESRC Centre for Business Research |volume= |issue=Working Paper No 274 |page=1 |publisher=[[University_of_Cambridge|University of Cambridge]] |date=September 2003 |url=http://www.cbr.cam.ac.uk/pdf/wp274.pdf |format=PDF |doi= |accessdate=2010-10-17 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5tZ21BvjA?url=http://www.cbr.cam.ac.uk/pdf/wp274.pdf |archivedate=2010-10-18 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

萨班斯-奥克斯利法案的主要条款包括建立上市公司会计监督委员会（Public Company Accounting Oversight Board），以制定审计报告编制标准；限制上市会计公司在审计时提供任何非审计服务；审计委员会成员独立性条款，在财务重述的情况下要求高管注销财务报告并放弃某些高管奖金；并增加公司与松散实体关系的财务披露。<ref name="Chhaochharia79"/>

2002年2月13日，由于企业违法行为和会计违规，SEC建议修改证券交易所法规。2002年6月，[[纽约证券交易所|纽约证券交易所]]宣布了一项新治理提案，并于2003年11月获SEC批准。NYSE最终提案的主要条款包括：<ref name="Chhaochharia79"/>
*所有公司必须拥有多数独立董事
*独立董事必须符合对独立董事的详细定义。
*薪酬委员会、提名委员会和审计委员应由独立董事构成。
*审计委员会所有成员必须具有金融知识。此外，审计委员会至少一名成员被要求具有会计或财务管理相关的专业知识。
*除了定期例会，董事会应召开无管理层参加的额外会议。

